title: Fashion Forward
description: When the Fashionistas launch a new line of brainwashing clothing, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls to stop the fashion trend before it's too late.

title: Oh, Daisy!
description: Buttercup is not a fan of Bubbles' newly created digital assistant.

title: How to Draw Blossom
description: The Powerpuff Girls character designer, Cheyenne Curtis, show you how to draw Blossom.

title: Speed Demon/Mojo Jonesin'
description: Mojo Jonesin':  When the children of Pokey Oaks become envious of the girls' superpowers, a mysterious figure offers them Chemical X. Now, the girls must fight their own classmates who have powers equal to their own./Speed Demon: The girls accidentally fly at the speed of light and when they arrive home, everything has changed. Fifty years have passed and the world has been taken over by Him.

title: Paste Makes Waste/Ice Sore
description: Paste Makes Waste: When Buttercup's taunting turns paste-eating classmate Elmer Sglue into a destructive Paste Monster, she gets out of a sticky situation by doing something against her tough nature, apologizing./Ice Sore: During a heat wave, Blossom discovers that she has a new power: ice breath. But when she doesn't use her new gift wisely, she gets a chilly reception from her sisters.

title: Bubbles' Beauty Blog But on Video
description: Bubbles' attempt to start her own beauty blog is thwarted by Blossom and Buttercup.

title: Air Buttercup
description: Buttercup tries to show off her basketball skills in the lunchroom to no avail.

title: Three Girls and a Monster/Monkey See, Doggy Two
description: Three Girls and a Monster: The girls are once again in a furious battle with a ferocious monster. But Blossom and Buttercup can't agree on how to fight the beast and Bubbles just wants everyone to get along./Monkey See, Doggy Two: Mojo has discovered a fatal flaw in his brilliant plan and decides to reenact it step-by-step. The girls think they're experiencing deja vu but it's really just Mojo working his maniacal mischief.

title: Bubbs and Donny Get the Mail
description: Bubbles and Donny are given their most daring mission ever: get the mail.

title: The Powerpuff Girls: A Documentary/Girls Gone Mild
description: The Powerpuff Girls a Documentary: A film student attempts to do a documentary on the Powerpuff Girls and learns catching these superheroes at rest is harder than he thought./Girls Gone Mild: When Parents Against Powerpuffs tell the girls that their superheroics are becoming too imitable, the girls must hold back on fighting crime.

title: The Tell Tale Schedulebot
description: After Blossom and Buttercup break Schedulebot, they'll do anything to keep the truth from coming out.

title: Silent Treatment/Sweet 'n' Sour
description: The Silent Treatment: When the girls go to see a silent movie with the Professor, they end up getting pulled into the film by an old-time villain./Sweet 'n' Sour: The girls must figure out how to beat Townsville's newest band of criminals: a group of adorable little animals.

title: Musclecup
description: Feeling inadequate as a superhero, Buttercup bulks up…to the max.

title: Superfriends
description: The new girl next door learns it's hard to be best friends with superheroes and soon starts hanging out with the wrong kind of kid, Princess.

title: Twisted Sister/Cover Up
description: Twisted Sister: The girls decide they need some help fighting crime so they create another Powerpuff Girl. But they don't get the combination of sugar, spice and everything nice quite right./Cover Up: Blossom and Bubbles learn that Buttercup has secretly been rubbing a security blanket before every battle to make herself a super fighter. Can the girls convince Buttercup that her strength is within?

title: 5 Reasons You're Actually Buttercup
description: 5 Reasons You're Actually Buttercup.

title: Rock Off Battle Music Video
description: The Powerpuff Girls rock out!

title: Ping Pong Z
description: It's "loser does the dishes" when the girls play ping pong in and around Townsville.

title: Horn, Sweet Horn
description: Bubbles convinces the Professor to test his new transmogrifying ray on her new friend Donny the Pony in an effort to help him become the unicorn he's always wanted to be. But when it turns Donny into a monster instead, she must stop him before he destroys Townsville!

title: Bye Bye, Bellum
description: The Mayor becomes dependent on the Powerpuff Girls after his assistant Ms. Bellum departs, leaving the girls so busy they accidentally hire the dangerous Bianca Bikini as his new assistant! When Bianca captures the Powerpuff Girls, the Mayor finds the tables turned and must rely on himself to help them.

title: Town and Out/Child Fearing
description: Town and Out: When the Professor gets a new job, the girls have to move away from Townsville. They try to make the best of it but it's just not the same. In fact, it's downright awful./Child Fearing: When the Mayor needs someone to babysit the girls for him, Mojo is unwittingly drafted. Little does Mojo know, taking care of three little girls can be a big hassle.

title: That's Not My Baby/Simian Says
description: That's Not My Baby!: The girls save a baby from a monster attacking Townsville but can't find the mother. Can these three superheroes manage to take care of one little baby?/Simian Says: When the Narrator is mysteriously bound and gagged, Mojo Jojo takes over his job, ordering the girls to steal for him all around Townsville.

title: Blundercup
description: Buttercup is knocked off-kilter by a mysterious force.

title: Bedtime
description: The girls need to get a good night's rest before family photo day, but they just can't seem to fall asleep!

title: Summer Bummer
description: When the beach is taken over by the most excellent Bro Sharks, will the Girls be gnarly enough to save the day?

title: How to Draw Buttercup
description: The Powerpuff Girls character designer, Cheyenne Curtis, show you how to draw Buttercup.

title: Octi Evil/Geshundfight
description: Octi Evil: The heinous Him toys with Bubbles' mind by speaking to her through Octi, her favorite stuffed animal. Following Him's orders, Bubbles picks a fight with her sisters that lands them all in a time-out./Geshundfight: The Amoeba Boys' ill-conceived plan to stand in Townsville Park all night in the rain leaves them with a nasty virus that's really something to sneeze at.

title: 5 Reasons You're Actually Blossom
description: 5 Reasons You're Actually Blossom.

title: Take Your Kids to Dooms Day
description: The Girls spend the day with the Professor at his boring office, only to find that the office comes with a terrible secret.

title: Halt and Catch Silico
description: When a series of negative articles about the Powerpuff Girls are posted on the Internet, the girls track them back to Silico.

title: Who's Got the Power?
description: Extended main title is set to music.

title: The Powerpuff Girls Movie
description: Blossom, Bubbles, and Buttercup--better known as the Powerpuff Girls--reveal the story of how they came to be the official protectors of the City of Townsville. When Professor Utonium first cooked up the Girls in his laboratory, he wasn't trying to give them superpowers. But when the Professor's mischievous monkey lab assistant Jojo knocked a dose of Chemical X into the mix, the Powerpuff Girls were born. While they have such powers as laser beam eyes, superhuman strength and the ability to fly at the speed of light, the Girls are only in Kindergarten. Although they don't mean to hurt anyone, their natural playfulness, coupled with their unnatural abilities, leads to some not-so-natural disasters and earns them the hatred of every man, woman and child in the city of Townsville. The girls are despondent, believing that their powers are evil and nobody loves them. Then Jojo slinks back onto the scene--but the Chemical X-plosion has mutated him into the evil genius Mojo Jojo. He convinces the Girls that he understands the pain of being an outsider, and lets them in on a plan that will endear them to all the people of Townsville--they will build a Help-the-Town-and-Make-it-a-Better-Place-Machine. The Girls immediately set to work gathering the necessary materials from all over the world. But what the Girls don't know is that Mojo Jojo has no intention of making Townsville a better place. In fact, he's planning on using the machine for his own nefarious purposes. Will the Girls realize the truth about Mojo as well as the true potential of their powers in time to really help the town and make it a better place?

title: Toast of the Town/Divide and Conquer
description: Toast of the Town: When the Mayor rubs Chemical X on his head for hair growth, all of him grows and stomps through Townsville./Divide and Conquer: When the Amoeba Boys learn how to divide, they multiply wreaking havoc as the many amoebas descend upon Townsville.

title: I'll Be Bake
description: Bubbles and Buttercup's good intentions are bad news for the cake Blossom is trying to bake.

title: The Trouble With Bubbles
description: When Bubbles is overworked, she uses her coding skills to come up with a new solution.

title: Cheep Thrills
description: After finding a baby monster in the park, Bubbles insists on adopting it without considering the consequences!

title: Stray Bullet
description: In order to save an innocent squirrel, Bubbles gives him a dash of Chemical X, giving him some super squirrel powers.

title: Lights Out!
description: When Bliss brings a new tech product to town, it's more powerful than imagined.

title: 5 Reasons You're Actually Bubbles
description: 5 Reasons You're Actually Bubbles.

title: Run, Blossom, Run
description: Blossom oversleeps and she'll stop at nothing to make it to school before she ruins her perfect attendance record!

title: Man Up 3: The Good, the Bad, and the Manly
description: After Bubbles gets blasted with Man Boy's beard ray, she wreaks havoc in the most manly and adorable way possible.

title: How to Draw Bubbles
description: The Powerpuff Girls character designer, Cheyenne Curtis, show you how to draw Bubbles.

title: Mojo Builds a Shelf
description: Mojo discovers the only thing more difficult than total world domination is DIY furniture.

title: Blissfully Unaware
description: Bliss uses her telekinetic powers to help the Professor make a more delicious dinner.

title: Bubbles of the Opera
description: When Bubbles gets a bad school photo, it sends her into an existential tailspin of darkness.

title: Seed No Evil/City of Clipsville
description: Seed No Evil: When a prehistoric caveman thaws out in Townsville, the girls must stop him from stealing the Mayor's seeds./City of Clipsville: The girls reminisce on their adventures in these new, never-before-seen clips!

title: Uh, Oh, Dynamo
description: Worried about his little girls' safety, the Professor creates Powerpuff Dynamo, a state-of-the-art protection system, to help them in battle.
